text: Maizurah Abdul Rahim (born 15 April 1999) is a Bruneian sprinter. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the women's 200 metres. She was the flag bearer for Brunei in the closing ceremony. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Bruneian female sprinters Category:Olympic athletes of Brunei Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics
